Place two blocks right next to each other so that they are touching. Create a second row by placing one block on top of each of the previous blocks. Create a third row by placing a single block on top of the left block of the pair on the second row. Create a fourth row by placing a block on top of the single block from row three. Place two additional blocks to the left of the block on row four, so that this row consists of three touching blocks. Create a fifth row by placing a block directly on top of the right-most block in row four. Place an additional block directly to the right of the single block on row five.
